I created a public and private parent page in my personal space with permissions appropriately set on each. I can then easily create child pages and understand their visibility. I want to put "everything" I do in Confluence, and having this personal scratchpad and knowing the visibility explicitly makes this easier.

One idea is to create these parent pages by default in new personal spaces such that a user could easily create things for themselves without having to change permissions on all the pages every time. 

It is also a concept that is very familiar (dropbox creates these by default for you). Given that users often struggle with what to do with their personal space, this could add a small improvement to the "blank personal space" problem.

