If the user has discovered and installed the OpenSearch plugin for their browser, Confluence will only start searching when the user presses enter in their browser search box. This is surprising since the search box built-in to confluence already does incremental search. Confluence should implement the suggestions part of the OpenSearch spec to bring the browser search closer to parity with built-in search.

Unfortunately, implementing this won't help CONF-15325 get implemented, but it won't hurt it either.

