Steps to reproduce:
- open Confluence editor;
- paste in a piece of *rendered* CSS; e.g.:
filter:progid:DXImageTransform.Microsoft.dropshadow(OffX=0,OffY=1,Color=#1b000000,Positive=true);
- observe as the page freezes and Chrome throws an error.

This happens even with the use of Code Block Macro. Chrome seems to get lost as it can't differentiate between the rendering metadata and the string itself.

Issue seems to be MacOS & Chrome-specific, doesn't occur in Firefox under Mac nor Chrome under Linux (not tested on Windows). If the pasted text isn't rendered, there's no error.

